fix(sage_meal_plan): convert Sage's emitted shapes into backend slot map (v0.1.9)

The auto-save fix in v0.1.6 (#9) wired the right METHOD (POST→PUT) and
ENVELOPE ({mealPlans:{<weekId>:slots}}), but it stuffed Sage's raw output
straight into the slots field. Sage emits a different shape than the
backend validator wants:

  Sage emits:    {sunday: {breakfast: "Recipe Name"}}
  Backend wants: {<slot-key>: {day:int, type:CapitalizedString, recipeId?}}

Result: even after #9, every Sage auto-save still 400'd at the slot
validator. Auto-save was effectively dead — invisible because the chat
reply went through fine and the silent failure was wrapped in `if
(saveResult.ok)`.

Companion PR `solidphp/oldfamilyrecipe#<TBD>` updates Sage's prompt to
emit the slot-keyed format directly. This PR makes the MCP tool tolerant
of BOTH the new shape and the legacy day-name shape (transitional, also
covers AI clients that improvise the format).

New `sageMealPlanToSlots(raw, weekId)`:
- Shape A (slot-keyed): pass through, normalize via existing
  `normalizeMealPlans` so day-name strings + lowercase types still work
- Shape B (day-name keyed): walk into each (day, meal-type, value) and
  reshape. Only emit slots with a real recipeId (UUID match) — slots
  without a recipeId would create empty backend rows, worse UX than
  dropping them and prompting the user to use `meal_plan_update`

When 0 slots survive conversion (Sage's plan was all new-recipe ideas
or all free-text titles), the auto-save is skipped and a friendly
message tells the user to use `meal_plan_update` manually. No more
silently saving nothing.

Tests: 6 new cases for `sageMealPlanToSlots` (Shape A passthrough,
Shape B conversion, free-text drop, object-with-recipeId, empty result,
nothing-matched user-facing message). 48/48 pass; tsc clean.

Bumps to v0.1.9 — publish when convenient.

